# Canonical list of Meshery's production remote providers.
#
# This is the single source of truth for PROVIDER_BASE_URLS across every install
# artifact (docker-compose files, the Helm chart, raw k8s manifests, the playground
# manifests, and the mesheryctl built-in fallback). Each line is `Name=URL`, where
# Name is the human-friendly provider name (and a valid value for the PROVIDER
# pre-selection env var) and URL is the provider's base URL.
#
# After editing this file, run `make generate-install` to propagate the change to all
# generated artifacts. `make check-install` (run in CI) fails if anything is out of sync.
# See docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-22-canonical-provider-urls-design.md.
Meshery=https://cloud.meshery.io
Layer5=https://cloud.layer5.io
